- Start is after first item, end is before second item - both fall in the gap
- `startIndex` will be 1 (pointing to second item)
- `endIndex` will be adjusted to 0 (last item before end)
- Since `startIndex > endIndex`, we should return empty series, but the buggy code proceeds to call `createCopy(1, 0)` which throws an exception

The fix needs to check if `startIndex > endIndex` after all adjustments:

```java
if (emptyRange || startIndex > endIndex) {
    TimeSeries copy = (TimeSeries) super.clone();
    copy.data = new java.util.ArrayList();
    return copy;
}
